						<summary>

						<p>Below the Jaina figure, cut out on the boulder outside the Cheṭṭippoḍavu cavern, on the Ummaṇāmalai hill.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Undated. In <hi rend="italic">Vaṭṭeḻuttu</hi> characters. (8th cent. A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged in the beginning. Records that the image was carved out by the (junior monk) Abinandan Bhaṭārar (II), the disciple of Arimaṇḍala Bhaṭārar, who was a disciple of (senior monk) Abinandan [Bhaṭārar] (I), who was probably a disciple of Kaṉakanandi Bhaṭārar of the monastery of Tirukāṭṭāmapaḷḷi at Kuṟaṇḍi.</p>						

						</summary>
